# AgeGate Harms

AgeGate Harms is a transparent scenario simulator for comparing age-verification approaches. It models access-control effectiveness, adult exclusion and deterrence, privacy/data-processing exposure, distributional burden, circumvention, and cost.

Version 0.1 contains **illustrative assumptions only**. It is designed to test the model and expose which evidence is needed, not to forecast the impact of a real law. The run also produces rank-correlation sensitivity diagnostics to prioritize evidence collection.

## Run the experiment

```bash
uv sync --extra dev
uv run agegate-run --simulations 50000 --seed 20260722
uv run pytest
```

Results are written to `results/`. Open `results/dashboard.html` for the self-contained static dashboard.

## Open the interactive simulator

```bash
uv sync --extra ui
uv run streamlit run app.py
```

## Project layout

```text
agegate-harms/
├── app.py
├── data/
